-- Global Funds Buy Net 20.4 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives
-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 2012-03-26T04:15:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-26/global-funds-buy-net-20-4-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors  bought a  net 20.4
billion rupees ($397.4 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
March 23, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, climbed 5.5 percent to 1.01 trillion rupees, or
34.8 percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds bought a net 94.6 million rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on March 23, according to preliminary data
given by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
